    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="131"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2222/493a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: The lack of a definite rule as
                    to the drafting of aliens is causing me extreme embarrassment. I am daily
                    besieged with the diplomatic representatives of countries with which we are at
                    peace begging me to define our policy so that they can reply to the large number
                    of letters of appeal which they are receiving. This has been going on for some
                    time but as September 1st approaches the representatives are growing more and
                    more insistent on a statement. In fact they begin to show considerable
                    resentment at not being told what the authorities intend to do.</p>
                <p>I have sent you several communications on this subject and hesitate on that
                    account to write again, but as there is a measure of justice in the complaint
                    that we have not stated our policy although aliens are being examined for
                    service by the military authorities, I feel it my duty to call the matter to
                    your attention.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
